Five people, all  females, were yesterday
feared dead while 12  others sustained various  degrees of injuries when  a trailer fell into a cliff in  Gurara local government  area of Niger State. LEADERSHIP Sunday  gathered that the
accident occurred around Kona Ayaba in
Sabon Kaida between Lambatta and Suleja. It was learnt that the trailer was carrying iron rods and 30 passengers
and was coming from Lagos state despite
the ban on inter state movement in Niger state. Eyewitness accounts revealed that the trailer which was heavily loaded with people and the iron rods momentarily lost control while trying to climb one of the hills along the road. The accounts revealed that the trailer was conveying 30 passengers compromising of 21 males and 9 females
among whom were three male children and five female children. It was learnt that those injured were three male adults, one female adult,
three male children and five female children while three female adults and
two female children died in the crash. The Suleja Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) Route Commander, Babatunde Onemola, confirmed that the accident took place about 11.40 am. He said immediately they got the distress
call, they began rescue, activities disclosing that the trailer with registration number UGG485XA was coming from Lagos. While speaking on the cause of the accident, he said that the weight
of the iron rod made it impossible for the trailer to climb the hilly road and thereby lost control and fell into the cliff.
He said that the remains of the deceased
had been deposited at the Sabon Wuse general hospital, while the injured victims were taken to a medical center
at Gawu Babangida for immediate medical attention.